Instruction: With the system assembled and the battery installed, probe along the series path to localize where the 12 V disappears. Starting from the PSU side, measure the voltage between the two-cable pair at the input of Control Module 1, then at its output; continue module by module (inputs and outputs of each control module) until reaching the load module. Identify the first point along the chain where the voltage between the two conductors drops from ~12 V to ~0 V, which will pinpoint the faulty module/cable segment or a polarity/connection error.
